{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh spinach and cherry tomatoes (optional) into it. Set aside.","Place garlic, onion, paprika and oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Add water and stock paste to mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, place salmon fillets into Varoma and season with salt and pepper. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>8-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until fish is cooked to your liking. Remove Varoma and transfer salmon into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Add risoni to mixing bowl and mix with aid of spatula, then cook <b>5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh cream and cornflour into it and lightly whisk together.","Add cream-cornflour mixture, lemon juice, salt and pepper to mixing bowl and heat <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved spinach and tomatoes and basil leaves and stir to combine with aid of spatula. Allow to rest for 2 minutes in mixing bowl. Flake reserved salmon into bite-sized pieces. Transfer risoni onto a serving platter and top with flaked salmon. Serve with lemon wedges (optional)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g fresh baby spinach leaves","100 g cherry tomatoes, cut into halves (optional)","1 garlic clove","1 brown onion, cut into halves (approx. 120 g)","2 tsp paprika","20 g olive oil","600 g water","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","3 fresh boneless, skinless salmon fillets (approx.150 g each)","¼ tsp salt, plus extra to season","2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to season","170 g dried risoni pasta","200 g pouring (whipping) cream","2 tsp cornflour","1 tbsp lemon juice","2 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only","1 lemon, cut into wedges, for serving (optional)"]}],"id":"r136625","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-q2TWQ8iFyzQ\/XZVRq96EAYI\/AAAAAAAAdR